---
/**
 * rest-api/0002 · Figure 3 — "PUT vs POST: who owns the target URI?".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0002-http-methods-and-status-codes.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, marker-end, …).
 *
 * The source SVG references arrowhead markers (arw, arwG) that the source page
 * defines ONCE in a body-level <svg><defs> block shared by all figures. To keep
 * this extracted figure self-contained and rendering byte-for-byte, the two
 * markers it uses are embedded here in a local <defs> (ids + fills unchanged so
 * the url(#arw)/url(#arwG) references resolve).
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 158"
        role="img"
        aria-label="If the client knows the target URI use PUT and it is idempotent; if the server assigns the URI use POST returning 201 with a Location header"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="300"
                y="16"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">WHO OWNS THE TARGET URI?</text
            >
            <rect
                x="210"
                y="28"
                width="180"
                height="34"
                rx="8"
                fill="#f1eee2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="300"
                y="49"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">Does the client know the URI?</text
            >
            <!-- YES branch -->
            <line x1="240" y1="62" x2="140" y2="92" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
            <text x="160" y="80" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >YES</text
            >
            <rect
                x="20"
                y="92"
                width="240"
                height="58"
                rx="9"
                fill="#eef5ee"
                stroke="#2f5d3a"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="140"
                y="112"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">PUT /users/42</text
            >
            <text x="140" y="129" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#244a2e"
                >replace-or-create at this address</text
            >
            <text x="140" y="143" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#244a2e"
                >idempotent — two calls → one user 42</text
            >
            <!-- NO branch -->
            <line x1="360" y1="62" x2="460" y2="92" stroke="#1f3a5a" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <text x="440" y="80" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >NO</text
            >
            <rect
                x="340"
                y="92"
                width="244"
                height="58"
                rx="9"
                fill="#eef2f5"
                stroke="#1f3a5a"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="462"
                y="112"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">POST /users</text
            >
            <text x="462" y="129" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >server assigns the URI</text
            >
            <text x="462" y="143" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >returns 201 + Location header</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The other axis: <code>PUT</code> replaces the <strong>whole</strong> resource;
        <code>PATCH</code> applies a <strong>partial</strong> modification. A partial body with
        <code>PUT</code> means "the omitted fields are now gone."
    </figcaption>
</figure>
